20:06.373 --> 20:08.484
Four minutes? Is that okay?
It's downstairs.

20:08.508 --> 20:10.553
-Do you know where the
coffee machine is? -Yes.

20:10.577 --> 20:12.721
The gyrotron works pretty
much like a Coke bottle.

20:12.745 --> 20:15.258
Except instead of blowing across
the top of the Coke bottle

20:15.282 --> 20:16.459
and changing the resonance,

20:16.483 --> 20:19.995
uh, it-it... you-you
do a electron beam.

20:20.019 --> 20:23.299
You have basically a little...

20:23.323 --> 20:25.033
filament down here,
like in a light bulb.

20:25.057 --> 20:26.369
It heats up,

20:26.393 --> 20:29.305
and this beam of
electrons comes up,

20:29.329 --> 20:30.763
and you get a resonance.

20:34.901 --> 20:38.013
So just as you take your Coke bottle,
you blow across the top of it,

20:38.037 --> 20:40.883
and the wind is creating
a compression wave

20:40.907 --> 20:44.453
and making a resonance, making
the sound go up higher,

20:44.477 --> 20:47.290
this thing is passing
an electron beam,

20:47.314 --> 20:48.891
and it creates an
electromagnetic resonance.

20:48.915 --> 20:52.561
You can almost imagine it like
a bunch of little laser beams,

20:52.585 --> 20:57.400
that you combine them into
a single coherent beam,

20:57.424 --> 20:58.825
which is the gyrotron beam.

21:00.393 --> 21:03.739
And then once this
ignites the plasma,

21:03.763 --> 21:06.599
the plasma itself heats
it and keeps going.

21:13.072 --> 21:14.574
That makes sense, kind of.

21:16.576 --> 21:19.522
Oh, no, doesn't it have to
be a glass one? Oh, man!

21:19.546 --> 21:21.490
- Well...
- We lose the analogy.

21:21.514 --> 21:23.025
What do you do with the can?

21:23.049 --> 21:25.394
- No, not a can.
- A bottle, a bottle.

21:25.418 --> 21:26.562
Oh, you wanted a bottle?

21:26.586 --> 21:29.398
Yeah, because you can blow
across the top of the bottle

21:29.422 --> 21:30.499
to make it resonate.

21:30.523 --> 21:32.968
