The greatest challenge is
to align these huge pieces

21:45.972 --> 21:49.518
to the millimeter tolerance,
to the accuracy that we need.

21:49.542 --> 21:50.619
It's really the magnets,

21:50.643 --> 21:53.346
the-the... what we call the
toroidal field magnets.

21:54.581 --> 21:57.426
These magnets make the main
magnetic field of ITER.

21:57.450 --> 21:59.695
They're the things that
hold this magnetic bottle,

21:59.719 --> 22:01.897
hold the plasma
inside the machine,

22:01.921 --> 22:02.998
and keep it away from the walls.

22:03.022 --> 22:06.101
And the accuracy that we
can install these magnets

22:06.125 --> 22:08.937
really is how smooth
the plasma will be

22:08.961 --> 22:10.373
and therefore how
well it performs.

22:10.397 --> 22:12.408
So the better we do
and the closer we get

22:12.432 --> 22:14.977
to the required position
for these magnets

22:15.001 --> 22:16.845
will really affect, for decades,

22:16.869 --> 22:18.146
the future performance of ITER.

22:18.170 --> 22:19.639
So that's a great
challenge for us.

